## ðŸŽ¯ Features

- **Responsive Design**: Fully responsive layout that works on mobile, tablet, and desktop
- **Multi-page Navigation**: Single-page application style navigation between sections
- **Interactive Elements**:
  - Mobile hamburger menu
  - Form validation with error messages
  - Smooth page transitions
  - Hover effects on buttons and project cards
- **Semantic HTML5**: Proper use of semantic elements for better accessibility and SEO
- **Modern CSS**: Flexbox, CSS Grid, variables, and animations
- **Clean Code Organization**: Well-structured and commented code

## ðŸ“„ Pages

1. **Home**: Hero section with introduction and call-to-action
2. **About**: Professional background, skills, and experience
3. **Projects**: Showcase of projects with descriptions and technologies used
4. **Contact**: Contact form with validation

## ðŸ› ï¸ Technologies Used

- HTML5
- CSS3 (Flexbox, Grid, Variables, Animations)
- JavaScript (ES6)
- Responsive Design Principles

## ðŸš€ Deployment

This project can be deployed on:

### GitHub Pages
1. Create a new GitHub repository
2. Upload all project files
3. Go to Settings > Pages > Select main branch
4. Your site will be published at `https://username.github.io/repository-name`

### Netlify
1. Drag and drop your project folder to Netlify dashboard
2. Or connect your GitHub repository for continuous deployment

### Vercel
1. Import your GitHub repository
2. Vercel will automatically deploy your site

## ðŸ“± Browser Compatibility

- Chrome (latest)
- Firefox (latest)
- Safari (latest)
- Edge (latest)

## ðŸ”§ Customization

To customize this portfolio for your own use:

1. Update personal information in the HTML file
2. Replace placeholder content with your own projects and details
3. Modify color scheme by changing CSS custom properties in the `:root` selector
4. Add your own images to the images folder and update references
5. Customize the form submission process (currently shows alert)

## ðŸ“ž Support

If you have any questions or need help with customization, please open an issue in the GitHub repository.

